In order to use this product properly, you need to download an Arduino  library called Softwire.h. 
This will guide you on how to download that package.

1. Open ArduinoIDE.
2. Copy and Paste the ASR012 code and paste it into the file.
3. On the left side of ArduinoIDE, Click on the bookshelf Icon, also called "LibraryManager"
4. In the library manager search bar, search up Softwire, There should be one created by Steve Marple,
   Select the dropdown menu and change the version to 2.0.10.
5. Click install.
